        <div
          class="c27"
        >
          <p
            class="c5 c28"
          >
            Front-end React Developer.
          </p>
          <p
            class="c5 c28"
          >
            Responsible for spearheading the development of back-office applications, catering to the internal administrative requirements of the company's business data.
          </p>
          <p
            class="c5 c28"
          >
            Initiated the creation of a comprehensive monorepo from the ground up using 
            <b
              class="c29"
            >
              Yarn Workspaces
            </b>
            , ensuring the development of full 
            <b
              class="c29"
            >
              TypeScript
            </b>
             applications.
          </p>
          <p
            class="c5 c28"
          >
            Implemented a robust Test-Driven Development (TDD) approach using 
            <b
              class="c29"
            >
              Jest
            </b>
             and 
            <b
              class="c29"
            >
              React Testing Library
            </b>
            .
          </p>
          <p
            class="c5 c28"
          >
            Implemented a sophisticated design system, utilizing a customized library of components using 
            <b
              class="c29"
            >
              Emotion.JS
            </b>
             alongside 
            <b
              class="c29"
            >
              Storybook
            </b>
             for comprehensive documentation.
          </p>
          <p
            class="c5 c28"
          >
            Established and optimized the frontend pipeline in 
            <b
              class="c29"
            >
              Jenkins
            </b>
            , utilizing parallel optimization for multiple stages.
          </p>
          <p
            class="c5 c28"
          >
            Basic knowledge in utilizing Terraform for storing environment variables in AWS.
          </p>
